Search for results and return in an exported CSV using the flexible search query tooling. Only data matching the specified conditions will be shown, not the full pass.\n
Example query for getting guide tyre results from 2022/07/26 10:33:00 onwards:
            
    POST {
        "query": {
            "range": {
                "pass_online_timestamp": {
                    "greater_than_equals": 1658831580000
                }
            }
        },
        "component_queries": {
            "component_category": ["GuideTyre"]
        },
        "sort": ["-pass_online_timestamp"],
        "total": true
    }

Search for results in the hierarchical format using the flexible search query tooling. Only data matching the specified conditions will be shown, not the full pass.
Example query for getting guide tyre results from 2022/07/26 10:33:00 onwards:
            
    {
        "query": {
            "range": {
                "pass_online_timestamp": {
                    "greater_than_equals": 1658831580000
                }
            }
        },
        "component_queries": {
            "component_category": ["GuideTyre"]
        },
        "sort": ["-pass_online_timestamp"],
        "limit": 500,
        "total": true
    }
            
Filter for 20 newest results skipping the first 10 results:
            
    {
        "sort": ["-pass_online_timestamp"],
        "limit": 20,
        "offset": 10,
        "total": true
    }
            
Filter for specific pass data:
            
    {
        "query": {
            "term": {
                "pass_pass_id": "<Pass Id>"
            }
        },
        "limit": 500,
        "total": true
    }
            
Note, the default maximum number of results returned in a query is 500. To see how many results are present in excess of the returned number, set "total" to true.


